procedures.name: Venipuncture
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), clinical safety laboratory assessments, and pregnancy testing.

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour pooled collection for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full or symptom-driven physical examination, including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Measurement of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and other clinically significant findings.

procedures.name: Oral Drug Administration
procedures.label: Study Drug Dosing
procedures.description: Administration of ALXN1840 tablets with 240 mL of water after an overnight fast.

procedures.name: Clinical Laboratory Assessment
procedures.label: Safety Labs
procedures.description: Analysis of blood samples for serum chemistry, hematology, and coagulation parameters.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine and/or serum pregnancy testing for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE/SAE Monitoring
procedures.description: Ongoing collection and assessment of adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: IV Cannulation
procedures.description: Placement of a cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Infectious Disease Screening
procedures.label: Viral Screening
procedures.description: Screening for Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV), hepatitis B, and hepatitis C.

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.label: UDS
procedures.description: Screening for drugs of abuse using a urine sample.

procedures.name: Alcohol Test
procedures.label: Alcohol Test
procedures.description: Test to screen for alcohol use.

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurement
procedures.label: Height/Weight/BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Medical History Collection
procedures.label: History Collection
procedures.description: Collection of participant medical history, demographics, Wilson disease history, and prior treatments.

procedures.name: Urination and Bowel Movement Monitoring
procedures.label: Intake/Output Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring and recording of urination and bowel movements.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Catheter
medicalDevices.label: Venous Catheter
medicalDevices.description: A catheter may be used for venous access for blood draws, not to be left in place for longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Device
medicalDevices.description: Completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Analytical instrument used to determine copper and molybdenum concentration in food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
